---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy">
  <div class="max-w-3xl">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-8">Last updated: March 2026</p>

    <div class="space-y-8 text-gray-600">
      <p>
        Runners in Need is a personal project operated by Nick Coury. There is no
        formal business entity behind it. No money changes hands on this platform
        &mdash; it exists solely to connect running gear donors with community
        organizers. This policy explains what data we collect, how we use it, and
        what rights you have.
      </p>

      <!-- 1. What We Collect and Why -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">1. What We Collect and Why</h2>
        <p class="mb-3">
          We collect only the information needed to operate the platform:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li>
            <strong>Email address</strong> &mdash; Used for authentication (magic links
            and optional Google OAuth sign-in) and to send you transactional
            notifications such as pledge updates.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Name</strong> &mdash; Displayed to other users so donors and
            organizers can identify each other.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Organization name</strong> (optional) &mdash; Shown on your profile
            and listings if you represent a group or running club.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Location</strong> &mdash; Used to match gear donations with nearby
            organizers. You choose how specific to make this.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Gear descriptions</strong> &mdash; The details you provide when
            posting a need or pledging gear, stored so listings can be displayed and
            matched.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- 2. What We Don't Collect -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">2. What We Don't Collect</h2>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li>
            <strong>Data from minors.</strong> This platform is used by adult organizers
            and donors. We do not knowingly collect information from anyone under 18.
            If you believe a minor's data has been submitted, please contact us and we
            will delete it promptly.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Financial data.</strong> No payments, credit card numbers, or
            banking information are collected. No money changes hands on this platform.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Tracking cookies or advertising identifiers.</strong> We do not use
            third-party analytics trackers, ad networks, or retargeting pixels.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <!-- 3. How We Use Your Data -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">3. How We Use Your Data</h2>
        <p class="mb-3">Your information is used to:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li>Authenticate your account and keep you signed in.</li>
          <li>Display your listings and profile to other users on the platform.</li>
          <li>Send transactional emails &mdash; pledge notifications, magic link
            sign-in codes, and direct messages between users.</li>
          <li>Match gear donations with organizer needs based on location.</li>
          <li>Respond to your support requests.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">
          We do not sell, rent, or share your personal data with third parties for
          marketing or any other purpose. Ever.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 4. Third-Party Services -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">4. Third-Party Services</h2>
        <p class="mb-3">
          We rely on two third-party services to operate the platform:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li>
            <strong>Cloudflare</strong> &mdash; Hosts the site and serves pages.
            Cloudflare processes incoming web requests, which means their servers see
            IP addresses and standard HTTP headers. Cloudflare provides built-in,
            privacy-friendly analytics (aggregated, no personal identifiers). We do
            not use any additional analytics tools. See
            <a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" class="text-[#2D4A2D] underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Cloudflare's privacy policy</a>.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Resend</strong> &mdash; Sends transactional emails on our behalf
            (magic link codes, pledge notifications). Resend processes your email
            address solely to deliver these messages. We do not send marketing or
            promotional emails through Resend or any other service. See
            <a href="https://resend.com/legal/privacy-policy" class="text-[#2D4A2D] underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Resend's privacy policy</a>.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">
          If you sign in with Google OAuth, Google processes your authentication
          according to
          <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" class="text-[#2D4A2D] underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google's privacy policy</a>.
          We receive only your name and email address from Google; we do not access
          your contacts, calendar, or any other Google data.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 5. Data Retention -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">5. Data Retention</h2>
        <p>
          Your data is kept for as long as your account is active. If you delete your
          account or request deletion, we will remove your personal data from our
          systems. Residual copies in backups may persist for a short time but are not
          used or accessed. To request account deletion, email us at the address below.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 6. Your Rights -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">6. Your Rights</h2>
        <p class="mb-3">You have the right to:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
          <li><strong>Access</strong> the personal data we hold about you.</li>
          <li><strong>Correct</strong> inaccurate or incomplete data.</li>
          <li><strong>Delete</strong> your account and all associated data.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-3">
          To exercise any of these rights, send an email to
          <a href="mailto:privacy@runnersinneed.org" class="text-[#2D4A2D] underline">privacy@runnersinneed.org</a>.
          We will respond within a reasonable timeframe.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 7. Cookies -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">7. Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          We use minimal cookies. The only cookies set are session cookies required to
          keep you signed in after authentication. These are essential for the site to
          function and cannot be disabled while using the platform. We do not use
          advertising cookies, tracking cookies, or any non-essential cookies. There is
          no cookie banner because there is nothing optional to consent to.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 8. CAN-SPAM Compliance -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">8. Email and CAN-SPAM Compliance</h2>
        <p>
          All emails we send are transactional &mdash; they relate directly to your
          account activity (sign-in links, pledge notifications, messages from other
          users). We do not send marketing or promotional emails. If you wish to stop
          receiving pledge notifications, you can adjust your notification preferences
          in your account settings or email us to opt out. You can also delete your
          account entirely to stop all emails.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 9. Changes to This Policy -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this policy from time to time. When we do, we will revise the
          "Last updated" date at the top. If we make significant changes to how we
          handle your data, we will notify you by email. Continued use of the platform
          after changes constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- 10. Contact -->
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">10. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          If you have questions about this privacy policy or how your data is handled,
          contact Nick Coury at
          <a href="mailto:privacy@runnersinneed.org" class="text-[#2D4A2D] underline">privacy@runnersinneed.org</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
